Tarew Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uizmaeleq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IzmaelEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/21/01 2:08:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions about a Fear CR</span><hr size=1> From my experience, there are two best (IMO) ways to breaking fear.<br>
<br>
1) SW break-in.  Zone in with 2-3, well balanced, as high level as possible groups.  Make it your usual exp grinding groups.  Have them all buff up as tightly as possible outside the portal, including shaman hp/sta buffs, resits, runes, SoW, haste, divine intervention on the key classes if you really wanna be a perfectionnist =P.  Invis them all and zone into fear all at once, then turn left 90 degrees and run until you bump into the wall (West wall, near South/West corner).  Bring all aggroed mobs to there, and have a paly or something camp just in case.  Kill all the mobs you just aggroed and brought with you to the camp, in an orderly and no panic manner.  If enchanters are getting too hard of a time mezzing, tank an add or two.  Keep enchanters up at any price.  Better lose a melee than an enc.  You will have to kill something in between 6 and 15 mobs in a row, until the camp is secure of wanderers.  You will be getting constant adds while fighting for sometime, so choose your main assist wisely, a smart and quick thinking tank can save the day.  Have the raid leader supervise the whole thing using third person view so he can take the decisions quickly.  After the camp has been secured, rest of the raid can zone in and run to the camp.<br>
<br>
If you have been wiped out, gather back at the fear portal, get mage summoned weapons and armor, rebuff / med, and run in again.  Repeat until camp secured.  Then proceed to punish the zone.<br>
<br>
<br>
2) Evac-break-in.  Have a couple balanced and experienced groups buff up and invis.  Each group should have at least one porter, two is much better (one wiz, one dru or something).  Zone in fear all together, then fight at the portal.  Kill at least one mob, mez the others.  After first mob dead, look around and if you see you can handle another one, kill it.  Do it as long as you feel you're controlling the situation.  When you feel you have too many mezzed adds and not enough mana, evac both groups at once.  Run back to fear, remed, zone in and continue killing.  Clear way to SW camp.  This can be done with one very good group.  I can tell you it's a real rush breaking fear on full pop with one group :P<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
There's a widely known way of breaking full pop fear from the North wall.  All run to North wall camp (safe spot), and die there while fighting the 4000 aggroed mobs, trying to allow the cleric(s) to camp out there.  Then cleric logs on and resses everyone.  Personnaly I've never been an addict of this way, because basicly you're looking at running through a full poped fear with see invis / undead mobs aggroing you, and you know you will die.  You aren't sure you will have a cleric camped out though.  So that's just a bit dicey, and I don't like dicey things in EQ.<br>
<br>
IMO, pickup fear raids are best when killing the repops, not breaking full pop fear.  You still achieve the same goals of farming the armor, yet you don't have to go through the ever so dangerous break in with a pickup raid. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22145>Iz.</a>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uiboozer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>iboozer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/21/01 2:59:56 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions about a Fear CR</span><hr size=1> Nice tips, I knew I would get some good advice from my fellow safehousers!<br>
<br>
We went back this morning and some large guild had cleared the zone right after the patch, so the CR ended up being easy. Walked in, rezzed who we could, looted others, ported out. The thing I feel bad about is that not everyone was online so there were 3 bodies still there when we left. Because of the patch all the corpses were naked, so there is no way to tell if they had been looted or not... hopefully they went in earlier than us and looted their stuff. There was one unfortunate person that ended up with a missing corpse (sorry longie), and I told him to petition. I don't know what the result of that was though because when I tried to follow up and make sure he got his stuff he wasn't online.<br>
<br>
One thing I was really pissed about is that all the time and deaths I spent moving all the bodies was a waiste. The dumb patch apparently moved all the bodies back to the spot they had died at, strangely only 1 body was still where I had left the nice huge pile.<br>
<br>
Well lesson learned... and some valuable info learned the hard way. I knew you guys would provide some awesome info though, THANKS A TON!! <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=46099">iboozer</a> - 51 Rogue of Bristlebane<BR>&lt;Legion of Obsidian Knights&gt;<BR>/tell me on Veeshan anytime!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhinterdir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HinterDir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/21/01 3:45:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions about a Fear CR</span><hr size=1> never have more than 10 people zone into fear <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> at once</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> or the zone is likely to crash.<br>
